<#GAPDoc Label="GraphInverseSemigroup">
<ManSection>
  <Oper Name="GraphInverseSemigroup" Arg="E"/>
  <Returns>A graph inverse semigroup.</Returns>
  <Description>
    If <A>E</A> is a directed graph (i.e. it satisfies <C>IsDirectedGraph</C>)
    then <C>GraphInverseSemigroup</C> returns the graph inverse semigroup
    <C>G(E)</C> where, roughly speaking, elements correspond to paths in the
    graph <C>E</C>. <P/>
    
    Given a directed graph <C><A>E</A>=(E^0,E^1,r,s)</C> the <E>graph inverse
      semigroup <C>G(E)</C> of <C>E</C></E> is the semigroup with zero generated
    by the sets <C>E^0</C> and <C>E^1</C>, together with a set of variables
    <M>\{e^-1 \mid e\in E^1\}</M>, satisfying the following relations for all
    <M>v,w\in E^0</M> and <M>e,f\in E^1</M>:
    <List>
      <Mark>(V)</Mark>
      <Item><M>vw = \delta_{v,w}\cdot v</M>,</Item>

      <Mark>(E1)</Mark>
      <Item><M>s(e)\cdot e=e\cdot r(e)=e</M>,</Item>
        
      <Mark>(E2)</Mark>
      <Item><M>s(e)\cdot e = e\cdot r(e) =e</M>,</Item>

      <Mark>(CK1)</Mark>
      <Item><M>e^{-1}f=\delta_{e,f}\cdot r(e)</M>.</Item>
    </List>
    (Here <M>\delta</M> is the Kronecker delta.) We define <M>v^{-1}=v</M> for
    each <M>v \in E^0</M>, and for any path <M>y=e_1\dots e_n</M> (<M>e_1\dots
      e_n \in E^1</M>) we let <M>y^{-1} = e_n^{-1} \dots e_1^{-1}</M>. With this
    notation, every nonzero element of <M>G(E)</M> can be written uniquely as
    <M>xy^{-1}</M> for some paths <M>x, y</M> in <M>E</M>, by the CK1 relation. 

    <Example><![CDATA[
gap> gr:= DirectedGraph( [ [ 2, 5, 8, 10 ], [ 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 8, 9, 10 ], 
> [ 1 ], [ 3, 5, 7, 8, 10 ], [ 2, 5, 7 ], [ 3, 6, 7, 9, 10 ], [ 1, 4 ], 
> [ 1, 5, 9 ], [ 1, 2, 7, 8 ], [ 3, 5 ] ] );
<directed graph with 10 vertices, 37 edges>
gap> S:=GraphInverseSemigroup(gr);
#I  the graph defines an infinite semigroup!
<graph inverse semigroup with 10 vertices, 37 edges>
gap> GeneratorsOfInverseSemigroup(S);
[ e_1, e_2, e_3, e_4, e_5, e_6, e_7, e_8, e_9, e_10, e_11, e_12, 
  e_13, e_14, e_15, e_16, e_17, e_18, e_19, e_20, e_21, e_22, e_23, 
  e_24, e_25, e_26, e_27, e_28, e_29, e_30, e_31, e_32, e_33, e_34, 
  e_35, e_36, e_37, v_1, v_2, v_3, v_4, v_5, v_6, v_7, v_8, v_9, 
  v_10 ]
gap> AssignGeneratorVariables(S);
gap> e_1*e_1^-1;
e_1e_1^-1
gap> e_1^-1*e_1^-1;
0
gap> e_1^-1*e_1;
v_2]]></Example>
  </Description>
</ManSection>
<#/GAPDoc>

